Frankly, I salute Fury's Edge for NOT forcing this to go FFA by sitting on Ragefire. Like they could. At. Any. Time. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=43032"><img src='http://mywebpages.comcast.net/theharters/NewImzy2.jpg' border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ukellimloh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kellim LoH</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/7/02 11:51:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Free For All on Ragefire 1-31 October ONLY</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  For example in order for me to fulfill my EQ dreams I have to leave a nice band of close friends and become a cog in the wheel of an &quot;uber&quot; guild in order to even have a chance at RF. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If you'd leave a &quot;nice band of close friends&quot; to get a shot at an item, then that reflects on your character, not the uber guilds.<br>
<br>
Unless you're in the top guild on the server, you accept the fact that you won't be seeing certain mobs in the very future, either because the mob is outside the capabilities of your guild/alliance, or because you'll lose races for that mob to guilds that are more capable (in raid terms) than your own.<br>
<br>
Generally speaking, that's an acceptable trade off for most people, the fact that you know your guildmates already, and feel comfortable and at home with them outweighs the benefits of joining the more capable guild.<br>
<br>
As for the issue of whether or not the top guilds would monopolize the spawn, I think it stands to reason that the bulk of the kills, upon it going FFA, would be had by the top raiding guilds on the server.<br>
<br>
The question is whether or not those guilds would kill Ragefire when they didn't have an actual main who needed the spawn.<br>
<br>
In any event, after seeing the controversy on this server surrounding Ragefire kills, I'm firmly convinced that I wrong in thinking a FFA system could be harmonious and would prefer to see the current system maintained as is.<br>
<br>
It may not be fair, it may not be perfect, but the alternative would be a huge headache. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=119554>Sir Kellim</a><BR><a href=http://reviction.lohnetwork.com/>Reviction</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/ugeldanmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GeldanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/8/02 8:49:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Free For All on Ragefire 1-31 October ONLY</span><hr size=1> You know... this is why I HATE trolling the boards sometimes, people just rip your thoughts apart and take them out of context to prove they're right. FE has been wonderful in comparison to many of the uber guilds of other servers. I have nothing against them and for the most part highly respect their membership and leaders. <br>
